node.text:
This January @xiaomi.global challenged me to make beautiful landscape photos at Baikal lake in the heart of Russian Siberia with smartphone #Mi10TPro

Watch this video where I accept the #BeyondThePostcard challenge and explain my approach to composition and light planning. @aleksandr_danadoev filmed me at the clearest ice of Baikal lake where we explored rocky islands, ice caves and even shoot milky way at night with the smartphone. We traveled by skates and by khivus (a sort of a boat with propeller at the back). Such an amazing experience to be able to glide and drift on the first thin ice. What could be better than a fresh #NewStart of the year with such an epic adventure? 

#ad at #Baikal #ShootLikeaPro

node.text:
Dombai mountains in Russia – film by @mavspel 
This fall I was exploring russian Caucasus mountains on expedition together with @audirussia
Hiking with @gitzoinspiresadventury backpack and traveler tripod.
В основе природы человека - любопытство и стремление к открытиям. Открытиям самого себя, через людей вокруг, через наш прекрасный мир. Даже если закрыты границы я всё равно 
стремлюсь прожить каждый день в движении, в поиске того самого кадра, в поиске 
совершенной композиции. Этот короткий фильм талантливого Саши @mavspel - о нашем 
путешествии в Домбай. Сентябрь и октябрь прошел для меня в открытии родных просторов 
Кавказа. Позади 7 тысяч километров и прекрасный проект с @audirussia - большое 
путешествие на “Кукушечке” Q7 из Москвы по Кавказу через Дагестан, Ингушетию и Домбай, 
Приэльбрусье. В такой долгой экспедиции совершенный и комфортный транспорт - это уже половина успеха фотографа. Сейчас я уже дома, с радостью вспоминаю теплый гостеприимный 
Кавказ - и скоро порадую вас свежими снимками. 
Music: Adrian Berenguer - The Journey (licensed at Artlist)
#Audi #ИскушениеПрогрессом #Q7 #NikonZ7 #gitzoinspires #Nikon #Russia #Caucasus

node.text: Recently, I photographed lotus flowers at the Astrakhan biosphere reserve in Russia using my @OnePlus 9 Pro smartphone with wide angle Hasselblad Camera for Mobile. These endless lotus fields are the largest in the world, and are located where the Volga river delta flows into the Caspian Sea. Using a wide angle lens smartphone helped me be more versatile when scouting for compositions and find angles very close to the flowers.  #YourBestShot #OnePlusPhotoAwards #Shotononeplus

node.text:
Time to start the new series on blooming Lotus flowers of Volga River delta in Russia. Beginning of August is the time when endless fields of lotus flowers bloom. Each flower blooming cycle is just 4 days. Basically only the very first night the flower can still close itself completely for the night, and then loosing it's force and fading it's colours. These fields considered to be the biggest in the world - and could be found where. Thanks to @fishfactory_hotel for this expedition to Volga river.
Время начать новую серию про цветение лотосов в дельте Волги в Астраханском заповеднике. Лотосовые поля здесь - самые обширные в мире! И цветение приходится на конец июля - начало августа. Цикл цветения обычно всего 4 дня, ведь это ускользающая красота лотосов, взошедших из грязи - символов чистоты и красоты. 
#Russia #lotus #Россия #лотос #Астрахань #

Swirling trails of stars above the Deadvlei, a white clay pan speckled with the 900-year-old tree skeletons, Quiver tree forest and Spitzkoppe across Namibia. 
The image series feature vortexes of multi-colored stars streaked across the sky like post-impressionist paintings. The Milky Way’s warm and cool tones intermix to create a kaleidoscopic vision of the sky above, and illuminate the barren desert landscape below. From the epic Namibia trip together with @jandre_namibia_photo_
#Namibia #gitzoinspires
#madewithluminar #Nikon

node.text:
When the nature takes it back. The dilapidated township of Kolmanskop, once been a wealthy settlement for diamond mining, now become part of the desert landscape. 
Desert winds once had blown the sand off the surface that was so rich in diamonds that even at nightfall, men on their hands and knees were able to gather gems glinting in the moonlight! But as soon as diamonds depleted the place was totally abandoned. 
Now photographers capturing the morning sunlight as it flows through the east-facing windows of each building. The fascinating rooms of many houses like school, hospital, living quarters with sand seeping into every crevice. 
#Namibia #kolmanskop #madewithluminar
#gitzoinspires #nikkor #Nikon #nikonz7
